{
  "texts": [
    "Especially when driven by RL, recommender systems can learn our subtle, private behavioral tendencies and use this information to drive coordinated action.",
    "Human agents can sometimes harness this power for their own purposes, such as depressing voter turnout to get an unpopular candidate elected.",
    "17 But algorithmic recommendation can have such population-level effects even without this sort of intentional guidance.",
    "Most viral trends take off more or less randomly.",
    "In any case, algorithmic recommendation's ability to combine deep individual personalization with large-scale collective influence makes it an especially powerful force acting on attention allocation."
  ]
}